<subSubSection id="CFE3650DB0388806FF7AFEBB991575E6" pageId="6" pageNumber="477" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="87463686B0388806FF7AFEBB9E637586" blockId="6.[166,1225,207,458]" pageId="6" pageNumber="477">Hosts: Arabian oryx (P = 100 %; I = 585); Ankole-Watusi (P = 100 %; I = 5); blackbuck (P = 50 %; I = 487.5 (20–1,091)); saiga antelope (P = 61.9 %; I =52.1 (5–187)); Barbary sheep (P = 40 %; I = 12 (3–21)); markhor (P = 81.8 %; I = 472.4 (4–2,212)); guanaco (P = 33.3 %; I = 5); llama (P = 66.7 %; I = 11.5 (1–22)); Bactrian camel (P = 100 %; I = 600).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="87463686B0388806FF7AFE3B991575E6" blockId="6.[166,1225,207,458]" box="[219,842,431,458]" pageId="6" pageNumber="477">Site of infection: abomasum, small intestine, caecum.</paragraph>
